-- Hungary Stocks: OTP Bank, Richter, FHB Move in Budapest Trading
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-05-18T12:45:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-17/hungary-stocks-otp-bank-mol-shares-move-in-budapest-trading.html
The benchmark  BUX (BUX)  index rose 1.5
percent to 16,530.66 by 2:21 p.m. in Budapest, snapping five
days of declines.  The following are among the most active shares in the
Hungarian market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  OTP Bank Nyrt. (OTP)  , Hungary’s largest lender with
operations in nine European countries, rose 3.2 percent to 3,404
forint, paring its weekly drop to 8.6 percent. Central and
eastern  Europe ’s economic outlook improved in May, the ZEW
Center for European Economic Research and Erste Group Bank AG
said.  Gedeon Richter Nyrt. (RICHT)  , Hungary’s biggest
drugmaker, added 2.2 percent to a one-week high of 36,500
forint.  Foldhitel es Jelzalogbank Nyrt.  (FHB HB), a Hungarian
mortgage lender, declined as much as 2.3 percent and last traded
0.4 percent lower at 510 forint.  Hungary ’s planned bank
transaction tax may lead to the country losing half of its bank
deposits within weeks, Mihaly Patai, president of the Bank
Association, told HVG.hu in an interview.  To contact the reporter on this story:
